                "paragraphOrdinal": 1,
                "paragraphTitle": "ANIMALS vs HUMANS",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "As we all know, animals can do many things that humans can't do. Birds can fly, fish can swim and breathe underwater, and monkeys can climb. Humans can't. Or can we? This week we talk to three amazing humans about their abilities."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 2,
                "paragraphTitle": "Interviewer: Luis, what exactly is a free climber?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "A free climber doesn't use ropes to help them climb, only to stop them from falling. Sometimes it's a little bit dangerous. I can't climb for very long because it's difficult and I get tired. I can climb about 500 meters in four hours."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 3,
                "paragraphTitle": "Interviewer: Seon-Yeong, can you really fly?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "Yes, I can! I'm a wingsuit flyer in my free time. Birds take off from the ground, but I can't. I jump from somewhere really high, like the top of a mountain or from a plane. I can fly for about four kilometers, and I'm usually in the air for two minutes."
                ]
              },
              {
                "paragraphOrdinal": 4,
                "paragraphTitle": "Interviewer: Ireen, you're a free diver – how long can you stay underwater?",
                "paragraphSubtitles": null,
                "paragraphContents": [
                  "I can hold my breath for about six minutes. I don't have an air tank, so I am very careful when I dive. I can dive about 80 meters down and then I need to come up again. I love it, it's so quiet underwater!"
                ]
              }
